  <section class="ipad-faq-section" id="faqs">
    <div class="ipad-container">
      <div class="ipad-section-header">
        <h2 class="ipad-section-title">iPad Repair FAQs</h2>
        <p class="ipad-section-subtitle">Common questions about iPad repair at Mobile Tech Lab in Winnipeg</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ipad-faq-list">
        <details class="ipad-faq-item">
          <summary class="ipad-faq-summary">
            <span>How much does iPad screen repair cost in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ipad-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ipad-faq-answer">iPad repair costs vary significantly by model — standard iPad models are the most affordable to repair while iPad Pro screens are the most expensive due to their ProMotion OLED assemblies. Contact us or use our online quote tool for a free upfront price on your specific iPad model.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ipad-faq-item">
          <summary class="ipad-faq-summary">
            <span>How long does it take to repair a cracked iPad screen in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ipad-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ipad-faq-answer">Most iPad screen replacements are completed same-day at our Winnipeg St. Vital location, typically within a few hours. iPad Pro screen repairs may take longer due to the complexity of the fused display assembly — we'll give you a time estimate when you drop it off.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ipad-faq-item">
          <summary class="ipad-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you use genuine Apple parts for iPad repairs?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ipad-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ipad-faq-answer">As an Apple Independent Repair Provider, we have access to genuine Apple parts and official diagnostics for iPad repairs. We also offer quality aftermarket parts at a lower price point — we'll explain both options and let you choose before starting any repair.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ipad-faq-item">
          <summary class="ipad-faq-summary">
            <span>What warranty do you offer on iPad repairs?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ipad-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ipad-faq-answer">Screen repairs carry a 30-day to lifetime warranty depending on the part tier selected. Battery replacements include a 90-day warranty, and most other component repairs carry a lifetime warranty on parts and labour.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ipad-faq-item">
          <summary class="ipad-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix a water-damaged iPad in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ipad-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ipad-faq-answer">Yes — we offer liquid damage recovery using ultrasonic cleaning and component-level diagnostics to assess what can be saved. Recovery success depends on the extent of the damage and how quickly the device was powered off after exposure — bring it in as soon as possible for the best outcome.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ipad-faq-item">
          <summary class="ipad-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you repair an iPad that won't turn on?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ipad-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ipad-faq-answer">Yes — a non-responsive iPad is often caused by a fully depleted battery, a failed display connection, or a software issue. We run free diagnostics to identify the root cause before recommending any repair so you know exactly what's wrong before spending anything.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ipad-faq-item">
          <summary class="ipad-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair iPad Pro screens in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ipad-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ipad-faq-answer">Yes — we repair all iPad Pro models including the latest M4 Pro. iPad Pro screens use ProMotion OLED fused displays that require specialized tools and model-specific parts — we stock them for all current iPad Pro generations at our St. Vital location.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ipad-faq-item">
          <summary class="ipad-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix an iPad home button or Touch ID?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ipad-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ipad-faq-answer">Yes — we repair and replace home buttons, Touch ID sensors, power buttons, and Face ID components across all iPad models. Most button repairs are completed same-day and carry a warranty on parts and labour.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ipad-faq-item">
          <summary class="ipad-faq-summary">
            <span>Do I need an appointment for iPad repair in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ipad-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ipad-faq-answer">No appointment is needed — walk-ins are welcome at both our St. Vital and Thompson locations during business hours. Calling ahead is helpful for iPad Pro repairs so we can confirm we have your model's specific parts in stock before your visit.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="ipad-faq-item">
          <summary class="ipad-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair iPads in Thompson, MB?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ipad-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="ipad-faq-answer">Yes — our Thompson location at 300 Mystery Lake Rd #1530 accepts iPad repairs and walk-ins Monday through Saturday 10AM–6PM. For iPad Pro or less common models, calling ahead helps us confirm parts availability before your visit.</p>
        </details>
